OL,3,CFirst Minister Vaughan Gething defends
OL,4,Ccuts to Wales' national museums
OL,6,FTom Giffard MS, shadow minister for
OL,7,Fculture, tourism and sport, said:
OL,8,F"This news is concerning not just for
OL,9,Fthe individuals who will be impacted,
OL,10,Fbut for all of us.
OL,12,F"Disproportionate funding cuts are
OL,13,Fputting the preservation of our shared
OL,14,Fheritage at risk, while the Labour
OL,15,FWelsh Government prioritises money for
OL,16,Fmore politicians.
OL,18,F"The Labour Welsh Government should
OL,19,Fscrap its vanity projects and use
OL,20,Fthose funds to protect our cultural
OL,21,Fhistory."
